   "source": [
    "Transform the images by applying below augmentations and convert it as Tensors"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 28898,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610191657656,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",
      "userId": "11974634202878261016"
     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "uhbRrUYvTEnt"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "stats = ((0.4914, 0.4822, 0.4465), (0.2023, 0.1994, 0.2010))\r\n",
    "train_tfms = tt.Compose([tt.RandomCrop(300, padding=4, padding_mode='reflect'), \r\n",
    "                         tt.RandomHorizontalFlip(), \r\n",
    "                         tt.RandomRotation(15),\r\n",
    "                         tt.ToTensor(), \r\n",
    "                         tt.Normalize(*stats,inplace=True)\r\n",
    "                         ])\r\n",
    "valid_tfms = tt.Compose([tt.ToTensor(), \r\n",
    "                         tt.Normalize(*stats)\r\n",
    "                         ])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "rAuk7PcRxB4Z"
   },
   "source": [
    "In the dataset, label is not provided separately . Image name contains label as dogs and cats like below.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "Here splitting image name using image.split with separator . it gives label as cat or dog .\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "'cat.7099.jpg',\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    " 'dog.6142.jpg',\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    " 'cat.2288.jpg',\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    " 'dog.2512.jpg',\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    " 'dog.9800.jpg'\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    " Assigned label 0 to dog and 1 to cat\r\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 51,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 944,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610192205052,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",

    "id": "fcTRTMsEWcCB"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def convert_label(label):\r\n",
    "  target = torch.zeros(2)\r\n",
    "  if label==\"dog\":\r\n",
    "    target[0]=1\r\n",
    "  else :\r\n",
    "    target[1]=1\r\n",
    "  return target"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "0j1oGjcEx4dQ"
   },
   "source": [
    "We can now create a custom dataset by extending the Dataset class from PyTorch. We need to define the __len__ and __getitem__ methods to create a dataset. We'll also provide the option of adding transforms into the constructor."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 52,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 931,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610192206965,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",
      "userId": "11974634202878261016"
     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "aGC1bTzUT7dM"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "class DogCatDataset(Dataset):\r\n",
    "    def __init__(self, image, root_dir,type_dataset,transform=None):\r\n",
    "        self.image = image\r\n",
    "        self.transform = transform\r\n",
    "        self.root_dir = root_dir\r\n",
    "        self.type_dataset = type_dataset\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "    def __len__(self):\r\n",
    "        return len(self.image)    \r\n",
    "    \r\n",
    "    def __getitem__(self, idx):\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        img_id = self.image[idx]\r\n",
    "        img_fname = self.root_dir + \"/\" + str(img_id) \r\n",
    "        img = Image.open(img_fname)\r\n",
    "        img = img.resize((300, 300))\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        if self.transform:\r\n",
    "            img = self.transform(img)\r\n",
    "        if self.type_dataset == \"train\" or self.type_dataset == \"val\":\r\n",
    "          img_label = convert_label(img_id.split(\".\")[0])\r\n",
    "          return img,img_label\r\n",
    "        else :  \r\n",
    "          return img"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "mUyNq0SMyHmY"
   },
   "source": [
    "Transforms can be chained using transforms.Compose. Here we are resizing the image to 300x300 before applying augmentations and convert it to tensors.\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "After converting an image to tensors, we are applying normalization."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 53,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 917,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610192209056,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",

     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "6B3ePJdGUpkb"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "train_ds = DogCatDataset(train_dataset,train_dir,\"train\",train_tfms)\r\n",
    "val_ds = DogCatDataset(val_dataset,train_dir,\"val\",valid_tfms)\r\n",
    "test_ds = DogCatDataset(all_test_images,test_dir,\"test\",valid_tfms)"
   ]
  },

    "Here is the sample tensors after applied transformations.label is present in each tensor as 1x2 tensor . index zero - 1 index one - 0 if the label is dog and index 0 -1 index 1 is 1 if the label is cat .(one hot encoding) "
   ]

   "source": [
    "def denormalize(images, means, stds):\r\n",
    "    means = torch.tensor(means).reshape(1, 3, 1, 1)\r\n",
    "    stds = torch.tensor(stds).reshape(1, 3, 1, 1)\r\n",
    "    return images * stds + means\r\n",
    "def show_image(dataset,index,stats=\"None\"):\r\n",
    "  image, label = dataset[index]\r\n",
    "  \r\n",
    "  if stats != \"None\":\r\n",
    "    image = denormalize(image, *stats)\r\n",
    "    image = image.reshape(3, 300,300)\r\n",
    "  plt.imshow(image.permute(1,2,0))\r\n",
    "  print('Label:', label)\r\n"
   ]
  },

   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "1rde1NJd7khv"
   },
   "source": [
    "Dog vs cat dataset is balanced dataset.The below module helps to view the number of images in each category"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 63,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 885,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610192301015,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",
      "userId": "11974634202878261016"
     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "mVcDYLTqhSAP"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "####Printing number of images in each category########\r\n",
    "def number_of_img_in_category(dataset):\r\n",
    "  class_dict = {}\r\n",
    "  for i in range(0,len(dataset)):\r\n",
    "    image,label = dataset[i]\r\n",
    "    if label[0] == 1:\r\n",
    "      label = 0\r\n",
    "    else :\r\n",
    "      label = 1\r\n",
    "    \r\n",
    "    if label in class_dict.keys():\r\n",
    "      class_dict[label]=class_dict[label]+1\r\n",
    "    else :\r\n",
    "      class_dict[label]=1\r\n",
    "  \r\n",
    "  return class_dict"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 64,
   "metadata": {

    "def show_batch(dl):\r\n",
    "    for images, labels in dl:\r\n",
    "        fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(12, 12))\r\n",
    "        ax.set_xticks([]); ax.set_yticks([])\r\n",
    "        denorm_images = denormalize(images, *stats)\r\n",
    "        ax.imshow(make_grid(denorm_images[:64], nrow=8).permute(1, 2, 0).clamp(0,1))\r\n",
    "        break"
   ]

    "Utility functions to check the device type and move the data to the existing device"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 70,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 2632,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610192351084,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",

     },

   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def get_default_device():\r\n",
    "    \"\"\"Pick GPU if available, else CPU\"\"\"\r\n",
    "    if torch.cuda.is_available():\r\n",
    "        return torch.device('cuda')\r\n",
    "    else:\r\n",
    "        return torch.device('cpu')\r\n",
    "    \r\n",
    "def to_device(data, device):\r\n",
    "    \"\"\"Move tensor(s) to chosen device\"\"\"\r\n",
    "    if isinstance(data, (list,tuple)):\r\n",
    "        return [to_device(x, device) for x in data]\r\n",
    "    return data.to(device, non_blocking=True)\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "class DeviceDataLoader():\r\n",
    "    \"\"\"Wrap a dataloader to move data to a device\"\"\"\r\n",
    "    def __init__(self, dl, device):\r\n",
    "        self.dl = dl\r\n",
    "        self.device = device\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "    def __iter__(self):\r\n",
    "        \"\"\"Yield a batch of data after moving it to device\"\"\"\r\n",
    "        for b in self.dl: \r\n",
    "            yield to_device(b, self.device)\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "    def __len__(self):\r\n",
    "        \"\"\"Number of batches\"\"\"\r\n",
    "        return len(self.dl)"
   ]
  },
  {

   "source": [
    "Here i  used accuracy to measure the model performance.i used imageclassificationbase class from jovian.ai tutorial code"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 139,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 996,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610196645622,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",
      "userId": "11974634202878261016"
     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "lDfl7Odhoiws"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "def accuracy(outputs, labels):\r\n",
    "    _, preds = torch.max(outputs, dim=1)\r\n",
    "    _,trues = torch.max(labels,dim=1)\r\n",
    "    return torch.tensor(torch.sum(preds == trues).item() / len(preds))\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "class ImageClassificationBase(nn.Module):\r\n",
    "    def training_step(self, batch):\r\n",
    "        images, labels = batch \r\n",
    "        out = self(images)                  # Generate predictions\r\n",
    "        loss = F.binary_cross_entropy(out, labels) # Calculate loss\r\n",
    "        return loss\r\n",
    "    \r\n",
    "    def validation_step(self, batch):\r\n",
    "        images, labels = batch \r\n",
    "        out = self(images)                    # Generate predictions\r\n",
    "        loss = F.binary_cross_entropy(out, labels)   # Calculate loss\r\n",
    "        acc = accuracy(out, labels)           # Calculate accuracy\r\n",
    "        return {'val_loss': loss.detach(), 'val_acc': acc.detach()}\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "    def validation_epoch_end(self, outputs):\r\n",
    "        batch_losses = [x['val_loss'] for x in outputs]\r\n",
    "        epoch_loss = torch.stack(batch_losses).mean()   # Combine losses\r\n",
    "        batch_accs = [x['val_acc'] for x in outputs]\r\n",
    "        epoch_acc = torch.stack(batch_accs).mean()      # Combine accuracies\r\n",
    "        return {'val_loss': epoch_loss.item(), 'val_acc': epoch_acc.item()}\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "    def epoch_end(self, epoch, result):\r\n",
    "        print(\"Epoch [{}], train_loss: {:.4f}, val_loss: {:.4f}, val_score: {:.4f}\".format(\r\n",
    "            epoch, result['train_loss'], result['val_loss'], result['val_acc']))\r\n",
    "    \r\n",
    "    "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 140,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 955,

    "'''class CatDogModel(ImageClassificationBase):\r\n",
    "    def __init__(self):\r\n",
    "        super().__init__()\r\n",
    "        self.network = nn.Sequential(\r\n",
    "            #32x300x300\r\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(3, 32, kernel_size=3, padding=1),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2),\r\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(32, 64, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2),\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(64, 64, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2),\r\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(64, 128, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2),\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(128, 128, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.MaxPool2d(2, 2),\r\n",
    "            nn.Conv2d(128, 256, kernel_size=3, stride=1, padding=1),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d(1),\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "            nn.Flatten(), \r\n",
    "            nn.Linear(256, 128),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.Linear(128, 64),\r\n",
    "            nn.ReLU(),\r\n",
    "            nn.Linear(64, 2),\r\n",
    "            nn.Sigmoid()\r\n",
    "        )\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "    def forward(self, xb):\r\n",
    "        return self.network(xb)'''"
   ]

    "import torchvision.models as models\r\n",
    "class CatDogModel(ImageClassificationBase):\r\n",
    "  def __init__(self):\r\n",
    "        super().__init__()\r\n",
    "        self.network =models.resnet18(pretrained=True)\r\n",
    "        self.network.fc = nn.Sequential(\r\n",
    "        nn.Linear(512, 2, bias = True),\r\n",
    "        nn.Sigmoid()\r\n",
    "        )\r\n",
    "  def forward(self, xb):\r\n",
    "    return torch.sigmoid(self.network(xb))"
   ]

   "source": [
    "It is always better to try the batch size first to know whether the cuda memory can accomodate the specified batch size"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 274,
   "metadata": {
    "colab": {
     "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
    },
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 2717,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610214132216,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",
      "userId": "11974634202878261016"
     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "u0B_7eFqnY5g",
    "outputId": "da68cdfe-25e4-45cb-9544-18bc0122817a"
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "images.shape: torch.Size([32, 3, 300, 300])\n",
      "out.shape: torch.Size([32, 2])\n",
      "out[0]: tensor([0.6231, 0.5545], device='cuda:0', grad_fn=<SelectBackward>)\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "def try_batch(dl):\r\n",
    "    for images, labels in dl:\r\n",
    "        print('images.shape:', images.shape)\r\n",
    "        out = model(images)\r\n",
    "        print('out.shape:', out.shape)\r\n",
    "        print('out[0]:', out[0])\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        break\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "try_batch(train_dl)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 275,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 1062,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610214136824,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",
      "userId": "11974634202878261016"
     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "GEdmLJxHE7DX"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@torch.no_grad()\r\n",
    "def evaluate(model, val_loader):\r\n",
    "    model.eval()\r\n",
    "    outputs = [model.validation_step(batch) for batch in val_loader]\r\n",
    "    return model.validation_epoch_end(outputs)\r\n",
    "\r\n",
    "def fit(epochs, lrs, model, train_loader, val_loader, opt_func=torch.optim.SGD):\r\n",
    "    torch.cuda.empty_cache()\r\n",
    "    history = []\r\n",
    "    optimizer = opt_func(model.parameters(), lrs)\r\n",
    "    for epoch in range(epochs):\r\n",
    "        # Training Phase \r\n",
    "        model.train()\r\n",
    "        train_losses = []\r\n",
    "        for batch in tqdm(train_loader):\r\n",
    "            loss = model.training_step(batch)\r\n",
    "            train_losses.append(loss)\r\n",
    "            loss.backward()\r\n",
    "            optimizer.step()\r\n",
    "            optimizer.zero_grad()\r\n",
    "        # Validation phase\r\n",
    "        result = evaluate(model, val_loader)\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        result['train_loss'] = torch.stack(train_losses).mean().item()\r\n",
    "       # print(result)\r\n",
    "        model.epoch_end(epoch, result)\r\n",
    "        \r\n",
    "        history.append(result)\r\n",
    "    return history"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {
    "id": "Gq2ds2oZA4le"
   },
   "source": [
    "# Training model and evaluating model parameters"
   ]

    "    train_losses = [x.get('train_loss') for x in history]\r\n",

    "# Predicting Test data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 191,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 910,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610201765557,
     "user": {
      "displayName": "santha lakshmi",
      "photoUrl": "",
      "userId": "11974634202878261016"
     },
     "user_tz": -330
    },
    "id": "FSc502KLfvGc"
   },
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "@torch.no_grad()\r\n",
    "def predict_dl(dl, model):\r\n",
    "    torch.cuda.empty_cache()\r\n",
    "    batch_probs = []\r\n",
    "    for xb in tqdm(dl):\r\n",
    "        probs = model(xb)\r\n",
    "        batch_probs.append(probs.cpu().detach())\r\n",
    "    batch_probs = torch.cat(batch_probs)\r\n",
    "    return batch_probs"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 193,
   "metadata": {
    "executionInfo": {
     "elapsed": 1015,
     "status": "ok",
     "timestamp": 1610201836994,
